def model_training(model, optimizer, criterion, model_save_version='v1', fig_save_version="v1"):
    model.train()
    h_dim = model.hidden_size
    num_layers = model.num_layers
    numPara = sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad)
    
    fig,ax = plt.subplots(2,1,tight_layout=True)
    fig.suptitle(f'{model.__class__.__name__} with {numPara} parameters (hidden={h_dim},layer={num_layers})')
    ax[1].plot(target,label='target')

    losses = []
    for epoch in range(epochs):
        loss_total = 0
        for i in range(len(x)):
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            out = model(x[i].view(1,lag,-1))
            loss = criterion(out.reshape(-1), target[i])
            loss.backward(retain_graph=True)
            optimizer.step()
            loss_total +=loss.detach().numpy()
            output[i] = out
        losses.append(loss_total/len(x))
        if epoch%20 ==0:
            print(f'Epoch #{epoch}: loss = {loss_total/len(x)}')

    ax[0].plot(losses,label=f'min {min(losses):.3f}')
    ax[0].set_ylim(0,max(losses)*1.1)
    ax[0].set_title(f'{criterion} with lr={lr}, lag={lag}')
    ax[0].set_xlabel('Epochs')
    ax[0].legend(loc = 'best')

    ax[1].plot(output.detach().numpy(),label=f'prediction')
    ax[1].set_title('Prediction vs Target')
    ax[1].set_xlabel('Training data')
    ax[1].set_ylabel('Daily Price Change')
    ax[1].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1),loc = 'best')

    plt.savefig(f'output/{model.__class__.__name__}_train_{fig_save_version}.png')
    plt.show()
    
    torch.save(model.state_dict(), f'output/{model.__class__.__name__}_state_{model_save_version}.bin')


def evaluation(model, names,fig_save_version="v1"):
    model.eval()
    h_dim = model.hidden_size
    num_layers = model.num_layers
    numPara = sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad)

    fig,ax = plt.subplots(1, len(names),tight_layout=True,sharex=True, figsize=(20,4))
    fig.suptitle(f'{model.__class__.__name__} with {numPara} parameters (hidden={h_dim},layer={num_layers})')

    for i, name_ in enumerate(names):
        data_train,label_train,data_test,label_test = create_train_test_datasets(testSize=1, lag=lag, features=features, names = [name_], shuffle=False)
        x = torch.Tensor(data_train)
        label_train.extend(label_test)
        ax[i].plot(label_train, label='actual')
        pred = model(x)
        pred = np.insert(pred.detach().numpy(),0, 0)
        ax[i].plot(pred,label='predicted')
        ax[i].axvline(x=len(data_train) - testSize, c='r', linestyle='--')
        ax[i].set_title(f'{name_}')
    ax[i].legend()
    plt.savefig(f'output/{model.__class__.__name__}_eval_{fig_save_version}.png')
    plt.show()

### Hyperparameter Inputs - Version 1

lag = 2       # number of preceeding days used for prediction 
testSize = 5  # number of trading days to be included in the test dataset
features =['chg_1d','chg_positive','chg_neutral','chg_negative'] #version 1
h_dim = 5       # number of hidden states in the RNN/LSTM models
num_layers = 1  # number of layers in the RNN/LSTM models
lr = 0.01       # learning rate
epochs = 100    # number of total training epochs

candidates = ['Tesla', 'Nikola', 'Nio', 'GM', 'Microsoft']

# Version 1: lag = 2, features =['chg_1d','chg_positive','chg_neutral','chg_negative'] 

model = LSTM(input_size=len(features), hidden_size=h_dim,output_size=1, num_layers=num_layers)

optimizer = torch.optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr)
criterion = torch.nn.L1Loss()

model_training(model, optimizer, criterion, model_save_version='v1', fig_save_version="v1")
evaluation(model, names=candidates,fig_save_version="v1")
